From dd6a146b094a9dc11b084d4df45bab2fb6a30142 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Tue, 5 May 2026 13:11:34 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 8: full-title cards + center-on-click +
 selected-chapter diff panel + drop edge labels
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Four storyboard improvements:

1. Full chapter titles. Cards now size to fit the entire title
   instead of clamping to two lines. Layout accepts a per-chapter
   heights map; estimateStoryboardCardHeight() approximates the
   card height from the title length and feeds the layout, so
   tier columns still stack without overlap.

2. Centre on click. Clicking a connection link in the storyboard
   detail rail (or any pathway that calls selectNodeRef.fn) now
   smooth-scrolls the canvas to put that card in the centre of
   the viewport. Direct node clicks don't recentre — the user
   is already looking at what they clicked.

3. Diff panel for the selected chapter. New flex-column row
   below the storyboard body shows the selected chapter's
   mini-diffs (re-using renderTourMiniDiffs). The panel takes
   up to 40% of the storyboard's vertical space and is updated
   on every chapter selection.

4. Drop edge labels. With overlapping rounded paths and many
   edges per node, the per-edge 'depends on' / 'verifies' /
   etc. labels clustered too densely to read. The colour-coded
   header legend carries the same information without the
   visual noise; the SVG labels are no longer emitted.
